## §2. PHASE DEFINITIONS — KINEMATIC CHAIN

Each phase maps to a **simple machine** with a governing **ODE**:

|Phase|Index|Name  |Role                    |Machine                    |Equation                               |
|-----|-----|------|------------------------|---------------------------|---------------------------------------|
|⚫    |0    |Black |Intake / Torsional Pull |Screw (camshaft)           |`I·ω̇ = τ_intake − b·ω`                 |
|⚪    |1    |White |Compression / Clamp     |Lever (cylinder head)      |`m·ẍ + c·ẋ + k·x = F_compress(t)`      |
|🟡    |2    |Yellow|Combustion / Ignition   |Wedge (spark plug)         |`E_ign = ∫₀^{τ_ign} P₀ e^{−t/τ_ign} dt`|
|🟤    |3    |Brown |Flywheel / Inertia Store|Pulley (crankshaft)        |`I·ω̇ = τ − b·ω`                        |
|🔴    |4    |Red   |Power Stroke / Work     |Inclined Plane (piston)    |`W = F·Δx`                             |
|🟢    |5    |Green |Exhaust / Clearing      |Wheel & Axle (rod)         |`m·ẍ + c·ẋ = F_exhaust(t)`             |
|🔵    |6    |Blue  |Regulation / Feedback   |Spring / Orbital (governor)|`m·ẍ + c·ẋ + k·x = F_feedback(t)`      |

