## §3. STATE SPACE & KERNEL UPDATES

### State Vector

```
Sys = (φ, S, E, F_B)

φ   ∈ Phase
S   = Entropy (structural pressure)
E   = Energy (capacity for work)
F_B = Fuel/Buffer (compression potential)
```

### Per-Phase Updates (Deterministic Kernel)

|Phase   |Update Rule                                      |
|--------|-------------------------------------------------|
|⚫ Black |`S ← compress(S)`                                |
|⚪ White |`assert λ_S < S < Ω_S ∧ ρ(S,E) > ρ₀`             |
|🟡 Yellow|`Ψ ← σ(F_B - 2e, φ)` ; `S ↦ S - ½Ψ` ; `E ↦ E + Ψ`|
|🟤 Brown |`F_B ← max(F_B, Ψ)`                              |
|🔴 Red   |`E ← E + Ψ` ; `S ← S - ½Ψ`                       |
|🟢 Green |`E ← E + ηΨ` ; `S ← S - ηΨ`                      |
|🔵 Blue  |`E ← (1-b)E + cS + aΨ`                           |

### Compression Ratio Proxy

```
ρ(S,E) = (|E| + ε) / (S + ε),  ε ≪ 1
```

### White Gate Predicate

```
White(S,E) := (λ_S < S < Ω_S) ∧ (ρ(S,E) > ρ₀)
```

