## §4. IGNITION FUNCTION (Yellow Phase)

### Sigmoid Ignition

```
Ψ(F_B) = 1 / (1 + e^{-φ(F_B - 2e)})

where:
  φ = (1 + √5)/2 ≈ 1.618034  (golden ratio)
  2e ≈ 5.436564              (threshold)
```

### Bounded Red Bernoulli Release

```
P       = κ_p · max(F_B, 0)              (pressure)
Φ       = C_d · A · √(2P/ρ)              (Bernoulli term)
cap_guard = max(0, 2(S - λ_S))           (safety guard)
Ψ_red   = max(0, min(Ψ_max, cap_guard, βΦ))
```

